PRAIRIE WOLF SOLAR, LLC
RATE SCHEDULE FERC NO. 1
Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service
Prairie Wolf Solar, LLC ("Prairie Wolf") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Supply Service") from the Prairie Wolf generating facility ("Prairie Wolf Facility").
Prairie Wolf is a wind turbine generating facility located in Coles County, Illinois. The Prairie Wolf Facility is interconnected to transmission facilities owned by Ameren Transmission Company of Illinois and under the operational control of the Midcontinent Independent System Operator, Inc. ("MISO").
This Rate Schedule FERC No. 1 sets forth Prairie Wolf's revenue requirement for Reactive Supply Service from the Prairie Wolf Facility. This Rate Schedule shall be effective upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
Prairie Wolf's monthly fixed revenue requirement consists of the charge for the Fixed Capability Component. Payment to Prairie Wolf shall be subject to Schedule 2 of MISO's Open Access Transmission Tariff.
MONTHLY REVENUE REQUIREMENT:
The Annual Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $905,000.00. The Monthly Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $75,416.67.
